== Ingredients

- 500g rice

- 2 carrots
- 5 celery sticks (25cm total)
- 1 red onion
- 1 tin tomatoes
- 500ml Chicken stock

- Chorizo (soft sausage, Sainsburys chorizo style sausage / Plant pioneers chorizo style shroomdogs)
- Mushrooms
- Peppers
- Prawn?
- Chicken?

== Method

- Sweat the hards (carrots, celery)
- Add the softs
- Deglaze with stock
- Salt to strong salty taste

- Fry sausage and other toppings

- Mix all together with rice in large flat pan
- Add 400ml of water
- Simmer until rice is aldente with lid (~10 mins)
- Simmer uncovered until mostly dry
- Transfer to 160C oven
- Cook until rice is mostly dry and crispy
- Transfer back to stove and cook for 3 mins on medium high heat (for delicious crust)

- Serve with lemon/lime and a dusting of salt
